main event: A bright object was observed over Pennsylvania on November 27, 1963 at 4:55 PM.
interesting points: The object was moving in a northwest direction.

The University of Pennsylvania Flower and Cook Observatory reported receiving many reports about a brilliant fireball that appeared over Pennsylvania on November 27, 1963 at 6:59 PM EST, as well as another fireball on December 7, 1963 around 2:10 PM.
The observatory requested information from the Air Force about these fireball sightings, as they seemed to have been witnessed from a wide area.
The report was not a UFO report, but rather a request for meteor data.
